<exercise checkit-seed="0003" checkit-slug="F2" checkit-title="Compound Interest">
  <statement>
      
                <p>Fahtima wants to have $1800 in a bank account that pays
                5.4% compounded semiannually after 16 years. 
                    <ol>
                      <li>How much money will should they invest today?</li>
                      <li>How much interest will they earn?</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
      
      <p>

      </p>
      
  </statement>
    
  <answer>
      
              <p>
              <ol>
                <li>They need to invest <m>\frac{P_0}{(1 + \frac{r}{n})^{nt}} = \frac{1800}{(1 + \frac{0.054}{2})^{2\cdot 16}} = </m> $767.39 today.</li>
                <li><m>P_0 - FV = 1800 - 767.39 = </m> $1,032.61 in interest will be generated.</li>
              </ol>
            </p>
  </answer>
</exercise>
